    "titleLine1": "BEHIND",
    "titleLine2": "THE CODE",
    "bioParagraph1": "I'm a designer who writes code and a developer who thinks in pixels. I started making websites when I was 14 because I thought it was cool that you could type some words and a page would appear. <span class=\"muted\">That feeling never went away.</span>",
    "pullQuote": "The gap between good and great is where I live.",
    "bioParagraph2": "Most of my days are spent obsessing over <span class=\"accent\">the 2px that makes a layout click</span>, the easing curve that makes an animation feel alive, the interaction that makes someone pause and think \"wait, that was nice.\"",
    "bioParagraph3": "When I'm not at my desk, I'm probably playing something on my Switch, discovering music I'll loop for three weeks straight, or taking long walks pretending I'm in a movie. <span class=\"muted\">Standard stuff.</span>",
